Commentary: 'wait' is the cry from Guptill after he drills the very full ball to cover. And they do... right up until the misfield from Hasnain the substitute... when they pinch the single

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, blocks it well. Looks like this game won't be complicated by menace of extra bounce

Commentary: lashes it past point! Oh this looks a batting beauty. No swing. Easy pace. And Boult makes matters even more easier by offering width. Good shot from Rizwan

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, opens the face looking for a single towards point, no such luck

Commentary: thumps it away! What a pull shot. It certainly looks like the Pakistan team has come out with a point to prove, especially against short bowling. Rizwan is back in his crease and hammers it away behind square leg
Commentary_short: Boult to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR runs

Commentary: shortish and outside off, goes at it hard hard, but since he's reaching out for the ball, he doesn't have all his balance and the cut shot goes to cover
Commentary_short: Boult to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: swings it away!. Haider is very very good at hitting the ball in the air, especially over the leg side field. Southee invites him to do so with a length ball angled into the pads and without Conway's last ditch dive at deep square leg, this would've been a boundary

Commentary: beaten by the bouncer. Southee sends one outside off and makes it climb over the batsman's shoulder. Haider is still caught on on his front foot, meaning when he goes for the hook shot, he has little chance of connecting
Commentary_short: Southee to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: sucked in by his own momentum and he's gone! Oh all those big hits, all that gung ho-ness. Pakistan want so desperately to win this powerplay. To completely dominate it. But this wasn't the ball. It's full. It's tailing in. New Zealand had bolstered the leg side, so Haider looks to open up and go over mid-off. He miscues it. And Williamson at mid-off takes a simple catch
Commentary_short: Southee to Haider Ali, OUT
Dismissal_text: Haider Ali c Williamson b Southee 8 (6m 4b 0x4 1x6) SR: 200.00

Commentary: back of a length on middle and off, defends
Commentary_short: Southee to Abdullah Shafique, no run

Commentary: straight up and it's taken by the bowler! A top edge to a half-hearted pull shot - half-hearted because Southee does not give him the room for such shenanigans. It's poor shot selection. it's born of Pakistan's need to whack NZ out of shape after the collapse in the first T20I. And it results in a second very very easy wicket.
Commentary_short: Southee to Abdullah Shafique, OUT
Dismissal_text: Abdullah Shafique c & b Southee 0 (1m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: punches a shortish delivery on off stump towards cover

Commentary: shortish and on off stump, guides it to point

Commentary: neat little tap to short third man as he waits on the ball with plenty of width to play that shot.

Commentary: goes back to a shortish ball on off stump and defends to point

Commentary: blocks a good length ball into the covers

Commentary: short and outside off - definitely there for the cut shot - but again Southee gets it to dart away past the flashing blade

Commentary: full on off stump, he drives to cover

Commentary: drills it through the covers. That's the risk in searching for swing. When it doesn't happen, the batsman can hit that fuller delivery on off stump through the line.

Commentary: pulls a short ball outside off to long leg

Commentary: full and outside off, drives smoothly to cover

Commentary: opens the face and slices a shortish ball on off stump to the left of the sweeper

Commentary: lets a good length ball outside off go through to the keeper

Commentary_short: Southee to Mohammad Hafeez, 1 run

He's trapped in his crease. He knows he has to play though because the ball is on off stump. Then it hits the deck and darts away past the outside edge. Glorious bowling.

Commentary: defends a fuller delivery on off stump
Commentary_short: Jamieson to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: loooooveeeeely shot! Hafeez seems to be the only one playing normal cricket. He's keeping the good ones out. He's constantly looking for a single. And if its in his arc, like this half-volley, he cracks it away to the boundary, this time through point

Commentary: bliiiiiiiiistering hit! The second the ball is angled into his pads, Hafeez is ready to flick it away. He also knows there is no one on the midwicket boundary so there's no need to keep it along the ground

Commentary: full and outside off, drives to the sweeper. Good batting. He's only run-a-ball but he's got a start, the kind that could build into a really big innings

Commentary: nearly chops on as Shadab looks for a cut to a ball that is too close to his body. The mis-hit though travels all the way to the fine leg boundary

Commentary: full and outside off, drives to cover

Commentary: starts with a yorker on off stump, Hafeez digs it out to point

Commentary: smears it to the boundary! See, this is what happens when you give yourself time at the crease. This is a good length ball outside off and he square drives it on the up to the point boundary. Absolutely majestic

Commentary: oohhhh this is clever! There is no malice in this shot. There isn't even the timing from the last boundary. There's only placement. He wants to beat third man on his left and he does. Beautiful batting

Commentary: goes for the dab to third man again and it wanders between keeper and first slip! Those two fielders are a good distance apart so he was playing a very intentional shot, looking for four once more

Commentary: extra bounce and Shadab, looking for the upper cut, can't quite connect
